import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.dates as dates
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from matplotlib import cm
import matplotlib as mpl
import numpy as np
%matplotlib notebook


def convert2Int(df, rangecolumn):
    for col in df.columns[rangecolumn]:
        df[col] = [ int(x.replace('.', '')) for x in df[col].values]
TourBW =   pd.read_csv("TourBW.csv", delimiter='\t',decimal = ',')  # 
convert2Int(TourBW, range(1,7))
TourBW = TourBW.ix[5:]
TourBW['avg_foreigner_stay'] = TourBW.ov_Foreigner.values / TourBW.Foreigner.values


def ReadFileAndPreproc(filename, rangecolumn):
    df = pd.read_csv(filename, delimiter='\t',decimal = ',')
    convert2Int(df, rangecolumn)
    df = df.ix[5:]
    df.set_index('Year', inplace = True)
    return df


austria = ReadFileAndPreproc("austria.csv", range(1,3))
belgien = ReadFileAndPreproc("belgien.csv", range(1,3))
france = ReadFileAndPreproc("france.csv", range(1,3))
italy = ReadFileAndPreproc("italy.csv", range(1,3))
japan = pd.read_csv("japan.csv", delimiter='\t',decimal = ',')
convert2Int(japan, range(1,3))
japan.set_index('Year', inplace = True)
netherland = ReadFileAndPreproc("netherland.csv", range(1,3))
sweden = ReadFileAndPreproc("sweden.csv", range(1,3))
switzerland = ReadFileAndPreproc("switzerland.csv", range(1,3))
uk = ReadFileAndPreproc("uk.csv", range(1,3))
usa = ReadFileAndPreproc("usa.csv", range(1,3))


nations = {'Austria' : 0,'Belgium':1, 'France' : 2 ,'Italy':3, 'Japan':4,'Netherlands':5, 'Sweden': 6, 'Switzerland':7, 'UK':8, 'USA':9}
nationslist = [austria, belgien,france, italy, japan, netherland, sweden, switzerland, uk, usa]
label = ['Austria','Belgium', 'France' ,'Italy', 'Japan','Netherlands', 'Sweden', 'Switzerland', 'UK', 'USA'] 
colors =['#DB15C1',  '#A70E0E', '#1557DB', '#26DB15', '#F6081B','#F67F08','#F4EC07','#15DBB7', '#557408', '#1D1867']

import matplotlib.animation as animation
titleSize = 13
labelsize = 11
legensize = 3
ticksize = 8
markersize = 15
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(11,8))
fig.canvas.draw()
beginYear = 1965
endYear = 2016
cur_x = 1965 

fig.suptitle('Tourists visiting Baden-Württemberg of Germany from 1965 to 2016', fontsize = titleSize )
ax1 = plt.subplot(2, 1, 1)

fig.text(0.06, 0.5, 'Average number of overnight', ha='center', va='center', rotation='vertical' ,fontsize = labelsize)
fig.text(0.5, 0.05, 'Size of circle stands for the count of tourists', ha='center', va='center', fontsize = labelsize)
#plt.cla()
ind = italy.index

for n in label:
    plt.plot(ind, nationslist[nations[n]].Overnight / nationslist[nations[n]].Arrive , label = n, color = colors[nations[n]])


                 

    
[line] = plt.plot([cur_x,cur_x],[1.2 ,3.2], c = 'grey',linewidth=2)    
#legend = plt.legend()

for spine in plt.gca().spines.values():
    spine.set_visible(False)


def draw(year):
    line.set_xdata([year, year])
    fig.canvas.draw_idle()
    
      
    plt.subplot(2, 1, 2 )
    plt.cla()
    plt.gca().set_ylim([1.2, 3.3])
    plt.gca().set_xlim([-0.5, len(label)])
    ovn = [nationslist[i].loc[year].avg_stay for i in sorted(nations.values())]
    arriv = [nationslist[i].loc[year].Arrive / 150 for i in sorted(nations.values())]
    plt.scatter(sorted(nations.values()), ovn, s=arriv, c=colors, marker="o")
    xtickslable = label
    plt.gca().set_xticks(np.arange(len(xtickslable)))
    plt.gca().set_xticklabels(xtickslable)  #, rotation = 11
    
    plt.gca().set_axis_bgcolor('#E8ECFF')  
    plt.grid(b=True, which='major', color='0.15', alpha = 0.14, linestyle='--')
    plt.annotate('year = {}'.format(int(year)), [3,3])
    for spine in plt.gca().spines.values():
        spine.set_visible(False)
    
    
def onscroll(event):
    global cur_x 
    if event.button == 'up':
        cur_x = min(endYear, cur_x +1)
    else:
        cur_x =  max(beginYear, cur_x -1)
    
    if cur_x < beginYear or cur_x > endYear:
        return   
    draw(cur_x)
    
    plt.gca().figure.canvas.flush_events()

def make_frame_mpl(curr):
    if curr + beginYear > endYear: 
        a.event_source.stop()

    return mplfig_to_npimage(fig) # RGB image of the figure

import io
import base64
from IPython.display import HTML
def video(fname, mimetype):
    
    video = io.open('BWTouris.mp4', 'r+b').read()
    encoded = base64.b64encode(video)
    video_tag = '{0} controls alt="test" src="data:video/{1};base64,{2}">'.format(', mimetype,  encoded.decode('ascii'))
    return HTML(data=video_tag)
